.TH "setActiveLocation" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
setActiveLocation \- set the ActiveLocation of the cluster
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]SdbDC.setActiveLocation(<location>)\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
SdbDC
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This function is used to set the specified location as ActiveLocation in the
cluster.
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
location ( \f[I]string, required\f[] )
.PP
Location name.
.IP \[bu] 2
The specified location needs to exist in the current cluster.
.IP \[bu] 2
When the value is an empty string, it means to delete the ActiveLocation of the
current cluster.
